I changed it to `children: PropTypes.oneOfType([PropTypes.shape({}), PropTypes.bool]),` with defaut prop of `null`. I also noticed that `datePicker` is also `children: PropTypes.oneOfType([PropTypes.shape({}), PropTypes.bool]),` in `Layout` component so i believe this is better for consistency.

I think the `PropTypes.element` is for React element as shown [here](https://reactjs.org/docs/typechecking-with-proptypes.html#proptypes) while `PropTypes.element.isReqiured` is for [requiring a single child](https://reactjs.org/docs/typechecking-with-proptypes.html#requiring-single-child). Since the `datePicker` prop seems to be used as a react element in the `GraphsContainer` component, I think using `PropTypes.element` with a default prop of `null` will work too.

