The `__dir__` method can return any sequence and will be converted into a list and sorted automatically. For example, if you return a set or any other sequence, `dir(obj)` will always be a list.

```python
class MyObj:
    def __dir__(self):
        return {'abc', 'xyz', 'def',}
obj = MyObj()
dir(obj)
['abc', 'def', 'xyz']
```

